		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>I don't see Warriors as "infringing" on our up-front snap&nbsp;aggro as much of a problem as most see it.&nbsp; Keeping the debuffers and crowd controllers safe on inc shouldn't be reserved to only 2 tank classes.&nbsp; Our roles in raids are far from as non-existant as they were back in Kunark, Velious, and Luclin... and having Warriors included in the trash clearing isn't hurting anyone.</P>
<P>It's like when (some) ShadowKnights claimed the sky was falling and we were going to be banished when Paladins got stun aggro upgrades... personally, I'd like faster aggro spells, since the spell is JUST aggro and designed to be JUST aggro...but arguing over a 0.5 second spell difference is like arguing over the possibility of 2 extra successful taunts out of 100 (if the RNG is steady)... it's not going to remove us from viability, or probably make a notable impact at all...</P>
<P>Might hurt our prides a bit... but honestly... Outside of competitive tanks, who's really going to care what class is in HoTT on a raid... as long as it's not them!</P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
