		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Knights are the tank mezzers of a raid. A warrior can certainly step up and take aggro to be more efficient and free the knight up and situationally you may need a warrior taking first aggro on really hard trash. However, its a knight strength and in a good team where folks aren't trying to one up each other it's pretty kewl. Even with mobs in camp a warrior has a much harder time controlling mobs that are going to be mezzed while they do hard dps. In that situation cyclone is often unusable, bazu not enough and attack a precarious thing. Knights have very many handy roles in raids including tanking.<br><div></div>	
