			>
			No I said knights are suited to MA a lot of appropiate content in raids. That it is a good role for them. My example in POP was chosen to show the to show that particular strength in an obvious manner. also it was particularily frustrating content for me to MA at the time, it was far easier for knights. When I am snared in DPOB the same advantage exists for them mitigated slightly by our new aggro discs and gear. In fact in general if adds do not hit too hard knights are simply the better add tanks for many reasons that I listed and you seem to have dismissed.<br><br>I never suggested your guild preffered Knight MA's. Like I said mine used me for a long time, that doesn't mean I ever thought i was as well suited to it as a good knight given appropiate dps mobs and healing.<br><br>You can call it a stereotype I call it an advantage. Yep, we're in DPOB. I use our knights there to MA. I also watch them handle aggro at a higher level of control than our warriors like always.<br><br><br>Like i said anyone knows spell slow will affect a caster a lot more than a melee and the reverse with slow. My problems with you post are many though.<br><br>In case you've forgotten...<br><br>You said there was no reason to prefer knight MA's in content anymore and sugested there wasn't a relevant aggro advantage. I've tried to show where in many cases knights do have an aggro advantage. They handle aggro on mezzable mobs far better, they handle aggro on mobs far better without damaging them, they have stronger ranged aggro and more conrtol over loose aggro which they can lock down more reliably and quickly aside from the use of taunt /ae taunt. Their aggro is far less affected by distance obviously because warrior aggro is melee and proc dependent. Similiarily physical debuffs generally have much less effect on knight aggro. I'd bet most knights would agree with these strengths whether you think they exist, or, not. They are part of class balance between us and should remain so imo.<br><br>Like i said before anyone can situationally MA and warriors are more suited to some trash, however, knight aggro control is generally better and is valuable. Who you decide to assign MA duty to is your deal, not mine.<br><br><br><div></div>	
