ean other classes cannot MA. It does mean Knights are particularily suited to it by virtue of their better ranged and snap aggro. Content will change and different emphasis will be put on your abilities. That doesn't mean they are not advantages that will pay out again. Just like warrior mitigation in group content. However, in DPOG we do use knights to MA and they are stronger at it for the reasons I mentioned. An MA does require some amount of judgement and sync with his team. Sometimes there are greater reasons than class advanatge to choose an MA. This doesn't change the fact your good ranged and snap aggro are valuable tools for an MA that warriors do not posssess in the same degree.<br><br>2) Our knights routinely maintain aggro on DPOB mobs while they are not in melee range. It's quite common in our raids and something i can't do in DPOB. I cannot get to the mobs in many events and lock aggro down as quickly as knights can in DPOB.<br><br>3) No it does have a bearing. Are you suggesting no warrior has ever broke a mez on your raids and had the add aggro non tanks? This is something that occurs to Knights far less often even taking into account new chanter abilities and new warrior aggro abilities.<br><br>4) I'm in the expansions we're talking about. I led my guild there from Time and MT'd before that. If there is anything i have had a very strong hand in in raid operations it's tanking. Other guilds prefer knight MA's as wel. Again, it is subject to the conditions of the event and the actual individuals involved. However, knight aggro is better suited to handle incoming adds than warrior aggro is on raids. That doesn't mean warriors can't do it. It just means it's a class advantage.<br><br>I haven't tried to rewrite your stance. I've made this simple argument several times. I fail to see where you have succesfully contested any of my points.<br><br></span></div>	
